LOCUS       HygR                     341 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  HygR (hph / APH(4)-Ia) is the E. coli hygromycin B
            4-O-phosphotransferase that confers hygromycin B resistance by
            ATP/GTP-dependent phosphorylation of the antibiotic's cyclitol
            4-OH..
